583 /* many compilers define _GNUC_ to some versions but then only implement
584  * what their idiot authors think are the "more important" extensions,
585  * causing enormous grief in return for some better fake benchmark numbers.
586  * or so.
587  * we try to detect these and simply assume they are not gcc - if they have
588  * an issue with that they should have done it right in the first place.
589  */
590 #if !defined __GNUC_MINOR__ || defined __INTEL_COMPILER || defined __SUNPRO_C || defined __SUNPRO_CC || defined __llvm__ || defined __clang__
591  #define ECB_GCC_VERSION(major,minor) 0
592 #else
593  #define ECB_GCC_VERSION(major,minor) (__GNUC__ > (major) || (__GNUC__ == (major) && __GNUC_MINOR__ >= (minor)))
594 #endif
595 
596 #define ECB_CLANG_VERSION(major,minor) (__clang_major__ > (major) || (__clang_major__ == (major) && __clang_minor__ >= (minor)))

903 /* count trailing zero bits and count # of one bits */
904 #if ECB_GCC_VERSION(3,4) \
905  || (ECB_CLANG_BUILTIN(__builtin_clz) && ECB_CLANG_BUILTIN(__builtin_clzll) \
906  && ECB_CLANG_BUILTIN(__builtin_ctz) && ECB_CLANG_BUILTIN(__builtin_ctzll) \
907  && ECB_CLANG_BUILTIN(__builtin_popcount))
908  /* we assume int == 32 bit, long == 32 or 64 bit and long long == 64 bit */
909  #define ecb_ld32(x) (__builtin_clz (x) ^ 31)
910  #define ecb_ld64(x) (__builtin_clzll (x) ^ 63)
911  #define ecb_ctz32(x) __builtin_ctz (x)
912  #define ecb_ctz64(x) __builtin_ctzll (x)
913  #define ecb_popcount32(x) __builtin_popcount (x)
914  /* no popcountll */
915 #else
916  ecb_function_ ecb_const int ecb_ctz32 (uint32_t x);
917  ecb_function_ ecb_const int
918  ecb_ctz32 (uint32_t x)
919  {
920  int r = 0;
921 
922  x &= ~x + 1; /* this isolates the lowest bit */
923 
924 #if ECB_branchless_on_i386
925  r += !!(x & 0xaaaaaaaa) << 0;
926  r += !!(x & 0xcccccccc) << 1;
927  r += !!(x & 0xf0f0f0f0) << 2;
928  r += !!(x & 0xff00ff00) << 3;
929  r += !!(x & 0xffff0000) << 4;
930 #else
931  if (x & 0xaaaaaaaa) r += 1;
932  if (x & 0xcccccccc) r += 2;
933  if (x & 0xf0f0f0f0) r += 4;
934  if (x & 0xff00ff00) r += 8;
935  if (x & 0xffff0000) r += 16;
936 #endif
937 
938  return r;
939  }

941  ecb_function_ ecb_const int ecb_ctz64 (uint64_t x);
942  ecb_function_ ecb_const int
943  ecb_ctz64 (uint64_t x)
944  {
945  int shift = x & 0xffffffffU ? 0 : 32;
946  return ecb_ctz32 (x >> shift) + shift;
947  }

949  ecb_function_ ecb_const int ecb_popcount32 (uint32_t x);
950  ecb_function_ ecb_const int
951  ecb_popcount32 (uint32_t x)
952  {
953  x -= (x >> 1) & 0x55555555;
954  x = ((x >> 2) & 0x33333333) + (x & 0x33333333);
955  x = ((x >> 4) + x) & 0x0f0f0f0f;
956  x *= 0x01010101;
957 
958  return x >> 24;
959  }

961  ecb_function_ ecb_const int ecb_ld32 (uint32_t x);
962  ecb_function_ ecb_const int ecb_ld32 (uint32_t x)
963  {
964  int r = 0;
965 
966  if (x >> 16) { x >>= 16; r += 16; }
967  if (x >> 8) { x >>= 8; r += 8; }
968  if (x >> 4) { x >>= 4; r += 4; }
969  if (x >> 2) { x >>= 2; r += 2; }
970  if (x >> 1) { r += 1; }
971 
972  return r;
973  }

975  ecb_function_ ecb_const int ecb_ld64 (uint64_t x);
976  ecb_function_ ecb_const int ecb_ld64 (uint64_t x)
977  {
978  int r = 0;
979 
980  if (x >> 32) { x >>= 32; r += 32; }
981 
982  return r + ecb_ld32 (x);
983  }

998 ecb_function_ ecb_const uint16_t ecb_bitrev16 (uint16_t x);
999 ecb_function_ ecb_const uint16_t ecb_bitrev16 (uint16_t x)
1000 {
1001  x = ((x >> 1) & 0x5555) | ((x & 0x5555) << 1);
1002  x = ((x >> 2) & 0x3333) | ((x & 0x3333) << 2);
1003  x = ((x >> 4) & 0x0f0f) | ((x & 0x0f0f) << 4);

1005

1011 {
1012  x = ((x >> 1) & 0x55555555) | ((x & 0x55555555) << 1);

1015  x = ((x >> 8) & 0x00ff00ff) | ((x & 0x00ff00ff) << 8);
1016  x = ( x >> 16 ) | ( x << 16);
1017

1210  /* converts an ieee half/binary16 to a float */
1211  ecb_function_ ecb_const float ecb_binary16_to_float (uint16_t x);
1212  ecb_function_ ecb_const float
1213  ecb_binary16_to_float (uint16_t x)
1214  {
1215  int e = (x >> 10) & 0x1f;
1216  int m = x & 0x3ff;
1217  float r;
1218 
1219  if (!e ) r = ecb_ldexpf (m , -24);
1220  else if (e != 31) r = ecb_ldexpf (m + 0x400, e - 25);
1221  else if (m ) r = ECB_NAN;
1222  else r = ECB_INFINITY;
1223 
1224  return x & 0x8000 ? -r : r;
1225  }

1227  /* convert a float to ieee single/binary32 */
1228  ecb_function_ ecb_const uint32_t ecb_float_to_binary32 (float x);
1229  ecb_function_ ecb_const uint32_t
1230  ecb_float_to_binary32 (float x)
1231  {
1232  uint32_t r;
1233 
1234  #if ECB_STDFP
1235  memcpy (&r, &x, 4);
1236  #else
1237  /* slow emulation, works for anything but -0 */
1238  uint32_t m;
1239  int e;
1240 
1241  if (x == 0e0f ) return 0x00000000U;
1242  if (x > +3.40282346638528860e+38f) return 0x7f800000U;
1243  if (x < -3.40282346638528860e+38f) return 0xff800000U;
1244  if (x != x ) return 0x7fbfffffU;
1245 
1246  m = ecb_frexpf (x, &e) * 0x1000000U;
1247 
1248  r = m & 0x80000000U;
1249 
1250  if (r)
1251  m = -m;
1252 
1253  if (e <= -126)
1254  {
1255  m &= 0xffffffU;
1256  m >>= (-125 - e);
1257  e = -126;
1258  }
1259 
1260  r |= (e + 126) << 23;
1261  r |= m & 0x7fffffU;
1262  #endif
1263

1265  }

1455 /* a floor() replacement function, should be independent of ev_tstamp type */
1456 static ev_tstamp noinline
1457 ev_floor (ev_tstamp v)
1458 {
1459  /* the choice of shift factor is not terribly important */
1460 #if FLT_RADIX != 2 /* assume FLT_RADIX == 10 */
1461  const ev_tstamp shift = sizeof (unsigned long) >= 8 ? 10000000000000000000. : 1000000000.;
1462 #else
1463  const ev_tstamp shift = sizeof (unsigned long) >= 8 ? 18446744073709551616. : 4294967296.;
1464 #endif
1465 
1466  /* argument too large for an unsigned long? */
1467  if (expect_false (v >= shift))
1468  {
1469  ev_tstamp f;
1470 
1471  if (v == v - 1.)
1472  return v; /* very large number */
1473 
1474  f = shift * ev_floor (v * (1. / shift));
1475  return f + ev_floor (v - f);
1476  }
1477 
1478  /* special treatment for negative args? */
1479  if (expect_false (v < 0.))
1480  {
1481  ev_tstamp f = -ev_floor (-v);
1482 
1483  return f - (f == v ? 0 : 1);
1484  }
1485 
1486  /* fits into an unsigned long */
1487  return (unsigned long)v;
1488 }
1489 
1490 #endif

1790 #define MALLOC_ROUND 4096 /* prefer to allocate in chunks of this size, must be 2**n and >> 4 longs */
1791 
1792 /* find a suitable new size for the given array, */
1793 /* hopefully by rounding to a nice-to-malloc size */
1794 inline_size int
1795 array_nextsize (int elem, int cur, int cnt)
1796 {
1797  int ncur = cur + 1;
1798 
1799  do
1800  ncur <<= 1;
1801  while (cnt > ncur);
1802 
1803  /* if size is large, round to MALLOC_ROUND - 4 * longs to accommodate malloc overhead */
1804  if (elem * ncur > MALLOC_ROUND - sizeof (void *) * 4)
1805  {
1806  ncur *= elem;
1807  ncur = (ncur + elem + (MALLOC_ROUND - 1) + sizeof (void *) * 4) & ~(MALLOC_ROUND - 1);
1808  ncur = ncur - sizeof (void *) * 4;
1809  ncur /= elem;
1810  }
1811 
1812  return ncur;
1813 }

1819  return ev_realloc (base, elem * *cur);

1933 /* make sure the external fd watch events are in-sync */
1934 /* with the kernel/libev internal state */
1935 inline_size void
1936 fd_reify (EV_P)
1937 {
1938  int i;
1939 
1940 #if EV_SELECT_IS_WINSOCKET || EV_USE_IOCP
1941  for (i = 0; i < fdchangecnt; ++i)
1942  {
1943  int fd = fdchanges [i];
1944  ANFD *anfd = anfds + fd;
1945 
1946  if (anfd->reify & EV__IOFDSET && anfd->head)
1947  {
1948  SOCKET handle = EV_FD_TO_WIN32_HANDLE (fd);
1949 
1950  if (handle != anfd->handle)
1951  {
1952  unsigned long arg;
1953 
1954  assert (("libev: only socket fds supported in this configuration", ioctlsocket (handle, FIONREAD, &arg) == 0));
1955 
1956  /* handle changed, but fd didn't - we need to do it in two steps */
1957  backend_modify (EV_A_ fd, anfd->events, 0);
1958  anfd->events = 0;
1959  anfd->handle = handle;
1960  }
1961  }
1962  }
1963 #endif
1964 
1965  for (i = 0; i < fdchangecnt; ++i)
1966  {
1967  int fd = fdchanges [i];
1968  ANFD *anfd = anfds + fd;
1969  ev_io *w;
1970 
1971  unsigned char o_events = anfd->events;
1972  unsigned char o_reify = anfd->reify;
1973 
1974  anfd->reify = 0;
1975 
1976  /*if (expect_true (o_reify & EV_ANFD_REIFY)) probably a deoptimisation */
1977  {
1978  anfd->events = 0;
1979 
1980  for (w = (ev_io *)anfd->head; w; w = (ev_io *)((WL)w)->next)
1981  anfd->events |= (unsigned char)w->events;
1982 
1983  if (o_events != anfd->events)
1984  o_reify = EV__IOFDSET; /* actually |= */
1985  }
1986 
1987  if (o_reify & EV__IOFDSET)
1988  backend_modify (EV_A_ fd, o_events, anfd->events);
1989  }
1990 
1991  fdchangecnt = 0;
1992 }

2090 /*
2091  * the heap functions want a real array index. array index 0 is guaranteed to not
2092  * be in-use at any time. the first heap entry is at array [HEAP0]. DHEAP gives
2093  * the branching factor of the d-tree.
2094  */
2095 
2096 /*
2097  * at the moment we allow libev the luxury of two heaps,
2098  * a small-code-size 2-heap one and a ~1.5kb larger 4-heap
2099  * which is more cache-efficient.
2100  * the difference is about 5% with 50000+ watchers.
2101  */
2102 #if EV_USE_4HEAP
2103 
2104 #define DHEAP 4
2105 #define HEAP0 (DHEAP - 1) /* index of first element in heap */
2106 #define HPARENT(k) ((((k) - HEAP0 - 1) / DHEAP) + HEAP0)
2107 #define UPHEAP_DONE(p,k) ((p) == (k))
2108 
2109 /* away from the root */
2110 inline_speed void
2111 downheap (ANHE *heap, int N, int k)
2112 {
2113  ANHE he = heap [k];
2114  ANHE *E = heap + N + HEAP0;
2115 
2116  for (;;)
2117  {
2118  ev_tstamp minat;
2119  ANHE *minpos;
2120  ANHE *pos = heap + DHEAP * (k - HEAP0) + HEAP0 + 1;
2121 
2122  /* find minimum child */
2123  if (expect_true (pos + DHEAP - 1 < E))
2124  {
2125  /* fast path */ (minpos = pos + 0), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2126  if ( ANHE_at (pos [1]) < minat) (minpos = pos + 1), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2127  if ( ANHE_at (pos [2]) < minat) (minpos = pos + 2), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2128  if ( ANHE_at (pos [3]) < minat) (minpos = pos + 3), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2129  }
2130  else if (pos < E)
2131  {
2132  /* slow path */ (minpos = pos + 0), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2133  if (pos + 1 < E && ANHE_at (pos [1]) < minat) (minpos = pos + 1), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2134  if (pos + 2 < E && ANHE_at (pos [2]) < minat) (minpos = pos + 2), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2135  if (pos + 3 < E && ANHE_at (pos [3]) < minat) (minpos = pos + 3), (minat = ANHE_at (*minpos));
2136  }
2137  else
2138  break;
2139 
2140  if (ANHE_at (he) <= minat)
2141  break;
2142 
2143  heap [k] = *minpos;
2144  ev_active (ANHE_w (*minpos)) = k;
2145 
2146  k = minpos - heap;
2147  }
2148 
2149  heap [k] = he;
2150  ev_active (ANHE_w (he)) = k;
2151 }
2152 
2153 #else /* 4HEAP */
2154 
2155 #define HEAP0 1
2156 #define HPARENT(k) ((k) >> 1)
2157 #define UPHEAP_DONE(p,k) (!(p))
2158 
2159 /* away from the root */
2160 inline_speed void
2161 downheap (ANHE *heap, int N, int k)
2162 {
2163  ANHE he = heap [k];
2164 
2165  for (;;)
2166  {
2167  int c = k << 1;
2168 
2169  if (c >= N + HEAP0)
2170  break;
2171 
2172  c += c + 1 < N + HEAP0 && ANHE_at (heap [c]) > ANHE_at (heap [c + 1])
2173  ? 1 : 0;
2174 
2175  if (ANHE_at (he) <= ANHE_at (heap [c]))
2176  break;
2177 
2178  heap [k] = heap [c];
2179  ev_active (ANHE_w (heap [k])) = k;
2180 
2181  k = c;
2182  }
2183 
2184  heap [k] = he;
2185  ev_active (ANHE_w (he)) = k;
2186 }
2187 #endif
2188 
2189 /* towards the root */
2190 inline_speed void
2191 upheap (ANHE *heap, int k)
2192 {
2193  ANHE he = heap [k];
2194 
2195  for (;;)
2196  {
2197  int p = HPARENT (k);
2198 
2199  if (UPHEAP_DONE (p, k) || ANHE_at (heap [p]) <= ANHE_at (he))
2200  break;
2201 
2202  heap [k] = heap [p];
2203  ev_active (ANHE_w (heap [k])) = k;
2204  k = p;
2205  }
2206 
2207  heap [k] = he;
2208  ev_active (ANHE_w (he)) = k;
2209 }
2210 
2211 /* move an element suitably so it is in a correct place */
2212 inline_size void
2213 adjustheap (ANHE *heap, int N, int k)
2214 {
2215  if (k > HEAP0 && ANHE_at (heap [k]) <= ANHE_at (heap [HPARENT (k)]))
2216  upheap (heap, k);
2217  else
2218  downheap (heap, N, k);
2219 }

2221 /* rebuild the heap: this function is used only once and executed rarely */
2222 inline_size void
2223 reheap (ANHE *heap, int N)
2224 {
2225  int i;
2226 
2227  /* we don't use floyds algorithm, upheap is simpler and is more cache-efficient */
2228  /* also, this is easy to implement and correct for both 2-heaps and 4-heaps */
2229  for (i = 0; i < N; ++i)
2230  upheap (heap, i + HEAP0);
2231 }

2445 {
2446  WL w;
2447

2449  return;
2450 
2451  --signum;
2452 
2453 #if EV_MULTIPLICITY

2456

2458  return;

2501 /* handle a single child status event */
2502 inline_speed void
2503 child_reap (EV_P_ int chain, int pid, int status)
2504 {
2505  ev_child *w;
2506  int traced = WIFSTOPPED (status) || WIFCONTINUED (status);
2507 
2508  for (w = (ev_child *)childs [chain & ((EV_PID_HASHSIZE) - 1)]; w; w = (ev_child *)((WL)w)->next)
2509  {

2511  && (!traced || (w->flags & 1)))
2512  {
2513  ev_set_priority (w, EV_MAXPRI); /* need to do it *now*, this *must* be the same prio as the signal watcher itself */
2514  w->rpid = pid;
2515  w->rstatus = status;
2516  ev_feed_event (EV_A_ (W)w, EV_CHILD);
2517  }
2518  }

2525 /* called on sigchld etc., calls waitpid */
2526 static void
2527 childcb (EV_P_ ev_signal *sw, int revents)
2528 {

2530 
2531  /* some systems define WCONTINUED but then fail to support it (linux 2.4) */
2532  if (0 >= (pid = waitpid (-1, &status, WNOHANG | WUNTRACED | WCONTINUED)))
2533  if (!WCONTINUED
2534  || errno != EINVAL
2535  || 0 >= (pid = waitpid (-1, &status, WNOHANG | WUNTRACED)))

3337 /* fetch new monotonic and realtime times from the kernel */
3338 /* also detect if there was a timejump, and act accordingly */
3339 inline_speed void
3340 time_update (EV_P_ ev_tstamp max_block)
3341 {
3342 #if EV_USE_MONOTONIC
3343  if (expect_true (have_monotonic))
3344  {
3345  int i;
3346  ev_tstamp odiff = rtmn_diff;
3347 
3348  mn_now = get_clock ();
3349 
3350  /* only fetch the realtime clock every 0.5*MIN_TIMEJUMP seconds */
3351  /* interpolate in the meantime */
3352  if (expect_true (mn_now - now_floor < MIN_TIMEJUMP * .5))
3353  {
3354  ev_rt_now = rtmn_diff + mn_now;
3355  return;
3356  }
3357 
3358  now_floor = mn_now;
3359  ev_rt_now = ev_time ();
3360 
3361  /* loop a few times, before making important decisions.
3362  * on the choice of "4": one iteration isn't enough,
3363  * in case we get preempted during the calls to
3364  * ev_time and get_clock. a second call is almost guaranteed
3365  * to succeed in that case, though. and looping a few more times
3366  * doesn't hurt either as we only do this on time-jumps or
3367  * in the unlikely event of having been preempted here.
3368  */
3369  for (i = 4; --i; )
3370  {
3371  ev_tstamp diff;
3372  rtmn_diff = ev_rt_now - mn_now;
3373 
3374  diff = odiff - rtmn_diff;
3375 
3376  if (expect_true ((diff < 0. ? -diff : diff) < MIN_TIMEJUMP))
3377  return; /* all is well */
3378 
3379  ev_rt_now = ev_time ();
3380  mn_now = get_clock ();
3381  now_floor = mn_now;
3382  }
3383 
3384  /* no timer adjustment, as the monotonic clock doesn't jump */
3385  /* timers_reschedule (EV_A_ rtmn_diff - odiff) */
3386 # if EV_PERIODIC_ENABLE
3387  periodics_reschedule (EV_A);
3388 # endif
3389  }
3390  else
3391 #endif
3392  {
3393  ev_rt_now = ev_time ();
3394 
3395  if (expect_false (mn_now > ev_rt_now || ev_rt_now > mn_now + max_block + MIN_TIMEJUMP))
3396  {
3397  /* adjust timers. this is easy, as the offset is the same for all of them */
3398  timers_reschedule (EV_A_ ev_rt_now - mn_now);
3399 #if EV_PERIODIC_ENABLE
3400  periodics_reschedule (EV_A);
3401 #endif
3402  }
3403 
3404  mn_now = ev_rt_now;
3405  }
3406 }

3408 int
3409 ev_run (EV_P_ int flags)
3410 {
3411 #if EV_FEATURE_API
3412  ++loop_depth;
3413 #endif
3414 
3415  assert (("libev: ev_loop recursion during release detected", loop_done != EVBREAK_RECURSE));
3416 
3417  loop_done = EVBREAK_CANCEL;
3418 
3419  EV_INVOKE_PENDING; /* in case we recurse, ensure ordering stays nice and clean */
3420 
3421  do
3422  {
3423 #if EV_VERIFY >= 2
3424  ev_verify (EV_A);
3425 #endif
3426 
3427 #ifndef _WIN32
3428  if (expect_false (curpid)) /* penalise the forking check even more */
3429  if (expect_false (getpid () != curpid))
3430  {
3431  curpid = getpid ();
3432  postfork = 1;
3433  }
3434 #endif
3435 
3436 #if EV_FORK_ENABLE
3437  /* we might have forked, so queue fork handlers */
3438  if (expect_false (postfork))
3439  if (forkcnt)
3440  {
3441  queue_events (EV_A_ (W *)forks, forkcnt, EV_FORK);
3442  EV_INVOKE_PENDING;
3443  }
3444 #endif
3445 
3446 #if EV_PREPARE_ENABLE
3447  /* queue prepare watchers (and execute them) */
3448  if (expect_false (preparecnt))
3449  {
3450  queue_events (EV_A_ (W *)prepares, preparecnt, EV_PREPARE);
3451  EV_INVOKE_PENDING;
3452  }
3453 #endif
3454 
3455  if (expect_false (loop_done))
3456  break;
3457 
3458  /* we might have forked, so reify kernel state if necessary */
3459  if (expect_false (postfork))
3460  loop_fork (EV_A);
3461 
3462  /* update fd-related kernel structures */
3463  fd_reify (EV_A);
3464 
3465  /* calculate blocking time */
3466  {
3467  ev_tstamp waittime = 0.;
3468  ev_tstamp sleeptime = 0.;
3469 
3470  /* remember old timestamp for io_blocktime calculation */
3471  ev_tstamp prev_mn_now = mn_now;
3472 
3473  /* update time to cancel out callback processing overhead */
3474  time_update (EV_A_ 1e100);
3475 
3476  /* from now on, we want a pipe-wake-up */
3477  pipe_write_wanted = 1;
3478 
3479  ECB_MEMORY_FENCE; /* make sure pipe_write_wanted is visible before we check for potential skips */
3480 
3481  if (expect_true (!(flags & EVRUN_NOWAIT || idleall || !activecnt || pipe_write_skipped)))
3482  {
3483  waittime = MAX_BLOCKTIME;
3484 
3485  if (timercnt)
3486  {
3487  ev_tstamp to = ANHE_at (timers [HEAP0]) - mn_now;
3488  if (waittime > to) waittime = to;
3489  }
3490 
3491 #if EV_PERIODIC_ENABLE
3492  if (periodiccnt)
3493  {
3494  ev_tstamp to = ANHE_at (periodics [HEAP0]) - ev_rt_now;
3495  if (waittime > to) waittime = to;
3496  }
3497 #endif
3498 
3499  /* don't let timeouts decrease the waittime below timeout_blocktime */
3500  if (expect_false (waittime < timeout_blocktime))
3501  waittime = timeout_blocktime;
3502 
3503  /* at this point, we NEED to wait, so we have to ensure */
3504  /* to pass a minimum nonzero value to the backend */
3505  if (expect_false (waittime < backend_mintime))
3506  waittime = backend_mintime;
3507 
3508  /* extra check because io_blocktime is commonly 0 */
3509  if (expect_false (io_blocktime))
3510  {
3511  sleeptime = io_blocktime - (mn_now - prev_mn_now);
3512 
3513  if (sleeptime > waittime - backend_mintime)
3514  sleeptime = waittime - backend_mintime;
3515 
3516  if (expect_true (sleeptime > 0.))
3517  {
3518  ev_sleep (sleeptime);
3519  waittime -= sleeptime;
3520  }
3521  }
3522  }
3523 
3524 #if EV_FEATURE_API
3525  ++loop_count;
3526 #endif
3527  assert ((loop_done = EVBREAK_RECURSE, 1)); /* assert for side effect */
3528  backend_poll (EV_A_ waittime);
3529  assert ((loop_done = EVBREAK_CANCEL, 1)); /* assert for side effect */
3530 
3531  pipe_write_wanted = 0; /* just an optimisation, no fence needed */
3532 
3533  ECB_MEMORY_FENCE_ACQUIRE;
3534  if (pipe_write_skipped)
3535  {
3536  assert (("libev: pipe_w not active, but pipe not written", ev_is_active (&pipe_w)));
3537  ev_feed_event (EV_A_ &pipe_w, EV_CUSTOM);
3538  }
3539 
3540 
3541  /* update ev_rt_now, do magic */
3542  time_update (EV_A_ waittime + sleeptime);
3543  }
3544 
3545  /* queue pending timers and reschedule them */
3546  timers_reify (EV_A); /* relative timers called last */
3547 #if EV_PERIODIC_ENABLE
3548  periodics_reify (EV_A); /* absolute timers called first */
3549 #endif
3550 
3551 #if EV_IDLE_ENABLE
3552  /* queue idle watchers unless other events are pending */
3553  idle_reify (EV_A);
3554 #endif
3555 
3556 #if EV_CHECK_ENABLE
3557  /* queue check watchers, to be executed first */
3558  if (expect_false (checkcnt))
3559  queue_events (EV_A_ (W *)checks, checkcnt, EV_CHECK);
3560 #endif
3561 
3562  EV_INVOKE_PENDING;
3563  }
3564  while (expect_true (
3565  activecnt
3566  && !loop_done
3567  && !(flags & (EVRUN_ONCE | EVRUN_NOWAIT))
3568  ));
3569 
3570  if (loop_done == EVBREAK_ONE)
3571  loop_done = EVBREAK_CANCEL;
3572 
3573 #if EV_FEATURE_API
3574  --loop_depth;
3575 #endif
3576 
3577  return activecnt;
3578 }

4083 static void noinline
4084 infy_add (EV_P_ ev_stat *w)
4085 {
4086  w->wd = inotify_add_watch (fs_fd, w->path,
4087  IN_ATTRIB | IN_DELETE_SELF | IN_MOVE_SELF | IN_MODIFY
4088  | IN_CREATE | IN_DELETE | IN_MOVED_FROM | IN_MOVED_TO
4089  | IN_DONT_FOLLOW | IN_MASK_ADD);
4090 
4091  if (w->wd >= 0)
4092  {
4093  struct statfs sfs;
4094 
4095  /* now local changes will be tracked by inotify, but remote changes won't */
4096  /* unless the filesystem is known to be local, we therefore still poll */
4097  /* also do poll on <2.6.25, but with normal frequency */
4098 
4099  if (!fs_2625)
4100  w->timer.repeat = w->interval ? w->interval : DEF_STAT_INTERVAL;
4101  else if (!statfs (w->path, &sfs)
4102  && (sfs.f_type == 0x1373 /* devfs */
4103  || sfs.f_type == 0x4006 /* fat */
4104  || sfs.f_type == 0x4d44 /* msdos */
4105  || sfs.f_type == 0xEF53 /* ext2/3 */
4106  || sfs.f_type == 0x72b6 /* jffs2 */
4107  || sfs.f_type == 0x858458f6 /* ramfs */
4108  || sfs.f_type == 0x5346544e /* ntfs */
4109  || sfs.f_type == 0x3153464a /* jfs */
4110  || sfs.f_type == 0x9123683e /* btrfs */
4111  || sfs.f_type == 0x52654973 /* reiser3 */
4112  || sfs.f_type == 0x01021994 /* tmpfs */
4113  || sfs.f_type == 0x58465342 /* xfs */))
4114  w->timer.repeat = 0.; /* filesystem is local, kernel new enough */
4115  else
4116  w->timer.repeat = w->interval ? w->interval : NFS_STAT_INTERVAL; /* remote, use reduced frequency */
4117  }
4118  else
4119  {
4120  /* can't use inotify, continue to stat */
4121  w->timer.repeat = w->interval ? w->interval : DEF_STAT_INTERVAL;
4122 
4123  /* if path is not there, monitor some parent directory for speedup hints */
4124  /* note that exceeding the hardcoded path limit is not a correctness issue, */
4125  /* but an efficiency issue only */
4126  if ((errno == ENOENT || errno == EACCES) && strlen (w->path) < 4096)
4127  {
4128  char path [4096];
4129  strcpy (path, w->path);
4130 
4131  do
4132  {
4133  int mask = IN_MASK_ADD | IN_DELETE_SELF | IN_MOVE_SELF
4134  | (errno == EACCES ? IN_ATTRIB : IN_CREATE | IN_MOVED_TO);
4135 
4136  char *pend = strrchr (path, '/');
4137 
4138  if (!pend || pend == path)
4139  break;
4140 
4141  *pend = 0;
4142  w->wd = inotify_add_watch (fs_fd, path, mask);
4143  }
4144  while (w->wd < 0 && (errno == ENOENT || errno == EACCES));
4145  }
4146  }
4147 
4148  if (w->wd >= 0)
4149  wlist_add (&fs_hash [w->wd & ((EV_INOTIFY_HASHSIZE) - 1)].head, (WL)w);
4150 
4151  /* now re-arm timer, if required */
4152  if (ev_is_active (&w->timer)) ev_ref (EV_A);
4153  ev_timer_again (EV_A_ &w->timer);
4154  if (ev_is_active (&w->timer)) ev_unref (EV_A);
4155 }
